ntries' health ministries. The WHO has stated that the reported numbers \"vastly underestimate the magnitude of the outbreak\", estimating there may be three times as many cases as officially reported.<ref name=\"CDC Estimating future number of cases\" /><ref name=\"Reuters\">{{cite news | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/10/22/us-health-ebola-who-idUSKCN0IB23220141022 | title=Official WHO Ebola toll near 5,000 with true number nearer 15,000 | work=[[Reuters]] | date=22 October 2014  |accessdate= 11 April 2015| author=Miles, Tom }}</ref><ref name=\"WHO 2014-08-22\">{{cite web|url=http://www.afro.who.int/en/clusters-a-programmes/dpc/epidemic-a-pandemic-alert-and-response/outbreak-news/4260-ebola-virus-disease-west-africa-22-august-2014.html|title=Ebola virus disease, West Africa|date=22 August 2014|publisher=WHO|accessdate=18 September 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140920193115/http://www.afro.who.int/en/clusters-a-programmes/dpc/epidemic-a-pandemic-alert-and-response/outbreak-news/4260-ebola-virus-disease-west-africa-22-august-2014.html|archivedate=20 September 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref><br>Note 3: Date is the \"as of\" date from the reference. A single source may report statistics for multiple \"as of\" dates.\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:right; white-space:nowrap; width:100%;\"\n|+Minor Ebola virus outbreaks by country and by date \u2013 30 July 2014 to most recent WHO / Gov update 30 August 2015 \n|-\n! rowspan=2 |Date ||colspan=2 | Aggregate Total || colspan=2 | Nigeria || colspan=2 | Senegal || colspan=2 | United States  || colspan=2 | Spain || colspan=2 | Mali || colspan=2 | United Kingdom || colspan=2 | Italy|| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:120px;\"|Refs\n|-\n! style=\"color: red;\" | Cases  || Deaths || style=\"color: red;\" | Cases || Deaths || style=\"color: red;\" | Cases || Deaths  || style=\"color: red;\" | Cases || Deaths || style=\"color: red;\" | Cases || Deaths|| style=\"color: red;\" | Cases  |