allery of Victorian and Edwardian Women Artists] at the University of Iowa\n* [http://latest-art.co.uk/ UK's ''Latest Art Magazine''] Polled Experts to list the 30 Greatest Women Artists. [http://latest-art.co.uk/pdfs/2/018_LA002.pdf Features] [http://latest-art.co.uk/pdfs/2/019_LA002.pdf six] [http://latest-art.co.uk/pdfs/2/020_LA002.pdf pages] [http://latest-art.co.uk/pdfs/2/021_LA002.pdf of] [http://latest-art.co.uk/pdfs/2/023_LA002.pdf artist] [http://latest-art.co.uk/pdfs/2/024_LA002.pdf profiles].\n* [https://www.myspace.com/colouringoutsidethelines Colouring Outside The Lines.] A UK zine interviewing female contemporary artists from around the world.\n* [http://db-artmag.com/en/63/ Female Formal]\n* [http://www.women-in-art.com The Great Female Artists from the Middle Age to the Modern Age]\n* [https://awarewomenartists.com/en/ AWARE : Archives of Women Artists, Research and Exhibitions (English - French)]\n* [[https://www.wendemuseum.org/programs/medea-insurrection-radical-women-artists-behind-iron-curtainhttps : exibition titled The Medea * [https://www.cornerhousepublications.org/publications/the-medea-insurrection/Insurrection: Radical Women Artists Behind the Iron Curtain (English-German)]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Women Artists}}\n[[Category:Women artists| ]]\n[[Category:Art history]]\n[[Category:Women ceramists]]\n[[Category:Women conceptual artists]]\n[[Category:Women costume designers]]\n[[Category:Women digital artists]]\n[[Category:Women film editors]]\n[[Category:Women glass artists]]\n[[Category:Women graphic designers]]\n[[Category:Women illustrators]]\n[[Category:Women metalsmiths]]\n[[Category:Women outsider artists]]\n[[Category:Women scenic designers]]\n[[Category:Women sculptors]]\n[[Category:Women textile artists]]\n[[Category:Women video artists]]\n", "name_user": "Po Mieczu", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eFurther reading", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Women_artists"}
{"title_page": "Henry Hungate", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2018}}\n'''Sir Henry Hungate''' (1598 \u2013 c. 1648) was an English politician who sat in the [[House of Commons of England|House of Commons]] in 1625 and 1626.\n\nHungate was the son of William Hungate of East Bradenham, Norfolk. He was educated at St Julian's and St Albans, Hertfordshire under Mr Heyward and was admitted at [[Caius College, Cambridge]] on 28 November 1613 aged 15. He was admitted at [[Gray's Inn]] on 8 February 1615. He was knighted on 20 April 1619. In 1625, he was elected [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Camelford (UK Parliament constituency)|Camelford]]. He was elected MP for  [[Newport (Cornwall) (UK Parliament constituency)|Newport]] in 1626. He was of St Martin-in-the-Fields, London and was probably sequestered as a royalist. His will was proved in 1648.<ref name=Venn>{{acad|id=HNGT613H|name=Hungate, Henry}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Portal|Cornwall}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|en}}\n{{succession box \n| title=[[Member of Parliament]] for [[Camelford (UK Parliament constituency)|Camelford]] \n| before=  [[Francis Cottington, 1st Baron Cottington|Sir Francis Cottington]]\n| before2= [[Edward Hare]]\n| with= [[Thomas Cotteel]]\n| years=1625\n| after= [[Edward Lyndley]]\n| after2= [[Thomas Monk|Sir Thomas Monk]] \n}}\n{{succession box \n| title=[[Member of Parliament]] for [[Newport (Cornwall) (UK Parliament constituency)|Newport]] \n| before=  [[John Eliot (statesman)|John Eliot]]\n| before2= [[Ralph Speccot]]\n| with= [[Thomas Williams (MP for Newport)|Thomas Williams]]\n| years=1626\n| after= [[Piers Edgcumbe]]\n| after2= [[William Killigrew (1606\u20131695)|Sir William Killigrew]]\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hungate, Henry}}\n[[Category:1598 births]]\n[[Category:1648 deaths]]\n[[Category:Members of the pre-1707 English Parliament for constituencies in Cornwall]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Gonville and Caius College, Cambridge]]\n[[Category:Members of Gray's Inn]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1625]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1626]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2018}}\n'''Sir Henry Hungate''' (1598 \u2013 c. 1648) was an English politician who sat in the [[House of Commons of England|House of Commons]] in 1625 and 1626.\n\nHungate was the son of William Hungate of East Bradenham, Norfolk. He was educated at St Julian's and St Albans, Hertfordshire under Mr Heyward and was admitted at [[Caius College, Cambridge]] on 28 November 1613 aged 15. He was admitted at [[Gray's Inn]] on 8 February 1615. He was knighted on 20 April 1619. In 1625, he was elected [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Camelford (UK Parliament constituency)|Camelford]]. He was elected MP for  [[Newport (Cornwall) (UK Parliament constituency)|Newport]] in 1626. He was of St Martin-in-the-Fields, London and was probably sequestered as a royalist. His will was proved in 1648.<ref name=Venn>{{acad|id=HNGT613H|name=Hungate, Henry}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|en}}\n{{succession box \n| title=[[Member of Parliament]] for [[Camelford (UK Parliament constituency)|Camelford]] \n| before=  [[Francis Cottington, 1st Baron Cottington|Sir Francis Cottington]]\n| before2= [[Edward Hare]]\n| with= [[Thomas Cotteel]]\n| years=1625\n| after= [[Edward Lyndley]]\n| after2= [[Thomas Monk|Sir Thomas Monk]] \n}}\n{{succession box \n| title=[[Member of Parliament]] for [[Newport (Cornwall) (UK Parliament constituency)|Newport]] \n| before=  [[John Eliot (statesman)|John Eliot]]\n| before2= [[Ralph Speccot]]\n| with= [[Thomas Williams (MP for Newport)|Thomas Williams]]\n| years=1626\n| after= [[Piers Edgcumbe]]\n| after2= [[William Killigrew (1606\u20131695)|Sir William Killigrew]]\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hungate, Henry}}\n[[Category:1598 births]]\n[[Category:1648 deaths]]\n[[Category:Members of the pre-1707 English Parliament for constituencies in Cornwall]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Gonville and Caius College, Cambridge]]\n[[Category:Members of Gray's Inn]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1625]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1626]]\n", "name_user": "Gazamp", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:AddedPortal:Cornwall", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henry_Hungate"}
{"title_page": "Berryessa Union School District", "text_new": "{{update|date=April 2012}}\nThe '''Berryessa Union School District''' operates thirteen [[elementary school]]s (K-5) and three [[middle school]]s (6-8) in [[Berryessa, San Jose, California]], [[United States|US]]. The district's superintendent is Dr. Roxane Fuentes. The Berryessa schools have tended to improve over the last decade,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.localschooldirectory.com/district-schools/4369377/Berryessa-Union-Elementary-School-District/CA#district_information@overview |title=Berryessa Union Elementary School District in California - Compare Ratings and Map of Schools Within the District |publisher=Localschooldirectory.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-13}}</ref> with the top performer, Ruskin Elementary School, having an API (Academic Performance Index) of 903 (out of 1000) as of fall 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.berryessasun.com/local/ci_10447155 |title=Berryessa - San Jose Mercury News |publisher=Berryessasun.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-13}}</ref> In 2011, Vinci Park Elementary School had the largest API increase in district history, having a 48-point increase. Graduates from the middle schools (Morrill, Sierramont and Piedmont) normally attend [[Piedmont Hills High School]] or [[Independence High School (San Jose, California)|Independence High School]]. Notable students include [[Jerry Yang (entrepreneur)|Jerry Yang]], who is the co-founder and former CEO of [[Yahoo!]], who went to Sierramont.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.4-traders.com/business-leaders/Jerry-Yang-31/biography/ |title=Jerry Yang - Biography |publisher=4-traders.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-13}}</ref> At Sierramont Middle School, Piedmont Middle School, and Morrill Middle School, there is also a Berryessa Chinese School.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bcs-usa.org/ |title=Berryessa Chinese School |publisher=Bcs-usa.org |date= |accessdate=2012-08-13}}</ref> The district also has an [[American football]] team called the Berryessa Cougars.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pages/BERRYESSA-COUGARS/257042297855 |title=Berryessa Cougars |publisher=Facebook |date= |accessdate=2012-08-13}}</ref> The BUSD association is an open resource organization with Minecraft as its main source of teaching.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pages/BERRYESSA-COUGARS/257042297855 |title=Berryessa Cougars |publisher=Facebook |date= |accessdate=2012-08-13}}</ref>\n\n\n{| border=\"1\"\n|+ '''School facts'''\n! School name\n! Students\n! FTE teachers\n! Pupil/teacher ratio\n|-\n| Berryessa Union Elementary School<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.education.com/schoolfinder/us/california/san-jose/berryessa-union-elementary/ |title=Berryessa Union Elementary School in San Jose, CA |publisher=Education.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-13}}</ref>\n| 16 || 1 || 16:1\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Brooktree Elementary School || 524 || 26\n| 20.2\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Cherrywood Elementary School || 523\n| 24 || 21.8\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Laneview Elementary School || 540 || 28.5\n| 18.9\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Majestic Way Elementary School || 528\n| 25 || 21.1\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Morrill Middle School || 1048 || 48 || 21.8\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Noble Elementary School || 511 || 24\n| 21.3\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Northwood Elementary School || 412 || 