s and Map of Schools Within the District |publisher=Localschooldirectory.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-13}}</ref> with the top performer, Ruskin Elementary School, having an API (Academic Performance Index) of 903 (out of 1000) as of fall 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.berryessasun.com/local/ci_10447155 |title=Berryessa - San Jose Mercury News |publisher=Berryessasun.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-13}}</ref> In 2011, Vinci Park Elementary School had the largest API increase in district history, having a 48-point increase. Graduates from the middle schools (Morrill, Sierramont and Piedmont) normally attend [[Piedmont Hills High School]] or [[Independence High School (San Jose, California)|Independence High School]]. Notable students include [[Jerry Yang (entrepreneur)|Jerry Yang]], who is the co-founder and former CEO of [[Yahoo!]], who went to Sierramont.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.4-traders.com/business-leaders/Jerry-Yang-31/biography/ |title=Jerry Yang - Biography |publisher=4-traders.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-13}}</ref> At Sierramont Middle School, Piedmont Middle School, and Morrill Middle School, there is also a Berryessa Chinese School.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bcs-usa.org/ |title=Berryessa Chinese School |publisher=Bcs-usa.org |date= |accessdate=2012-08-13}}</ref> The district also has an [[American football]] team called the Berryessa Cougars.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pages/BERRYESSA-COUGARS/257042297855 |title=Berryessa Cougars |publisher=Facebook |date= |accessdate=2012-08-13}}</ref> The BUSD association is an open resource organization with Minecraft as its main source of teaching.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pages/BERRYESSA-COUGARS/257042297855 |title=Berryessa Cougars |publisher=Facebook |date= |accessdate=2012-08-13}}</ref>\n\n\n{| border=\"1\"\n|+ '''School facts'''\n! School name\n! Students\n! FTE teachers\n! Pupil/teacher ratio\n|-\n| Berryessa Union Elementary School<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.education.com/schoolfinder/us/california/san-jose/berryessa-union-elementary/ |title=Berryessa Union Elementary School in San Jose, CA |publisher=Education.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-13}}</ref>\n| 16 || 1 || 16:1\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Brooktree Elementary School || 524 || 26\n| 20.2\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Cherrywood Elementary School || 523\n| 24 || 21.8\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Laneview Elementary School || 540 || 28.5\n| 18.9\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Majestic Way Elementary School || 528\n| 25 || 21.1\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Morrill Middle School || 1048 || 48 || 21.8\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Noble Elementary School || 511 || 24\n| 21.3\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Northwood Elementary School || 412 || 22\n| 18.7\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Piedmont Middle School || 991 || 41 || 24.2\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Ruskin Elementary School || 621 || 29\n| 21.4\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Sierramont Middle School || 1011 || 42\n| 24.1\n<!--\n|-----\n| align=\"right\" | Notes\n| colspan=\"3\" | (replace this with notes and un-comment line) -->\n|-\n| Summerdale Elemen